{{notability|date=February 2014}}

'''Living Garment of God''', Living [[Nature]], so called by [[Johann Wolfgang von Goethe|Goethe]], nature being viewed by him as the garment, or vesture, with which [[God]] invests himself so as to reveal and impart Himself to man.

